HEADWORD: Dry-shod
<hw>Dry"-shod`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Without wetting the
feet; having or keeping the feet or shoes dry; <as>as, a land bridge
over which man and beasts could have crossed
<ex>dry-shod</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dry-stone</ent>⟦br⟧
